    {
      "name": "Chapter 8 — Expand (Resolution Tree)",
      "description": "Expand shows WHY a permission exists by returning the full resolution tree — all paths that grant the relationship.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Expand — viewer on document:roadmap",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tuple_key\": { \"relation\": \"viewer\", \"object\": \"document:roadmap\" },\n  \"authorization_model_id\": \"{{model_id}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/stores/{{store_id}}/expand",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["stores", "{{store_id}}", "expand"]
            },
            "description": "SDK: Expand. Returns the userset tree for viewer on document:roadmap — the union of direct users, editor (which folds in owner + editor-from-parent), and viewer-from-parent."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Appendix — Other tuple ops",
      "description": "Reading and deleting tuples, plus store cleanup — endpoints not exercised in the CLI narration but part of the OpenFGA API surface.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Read Tuples — all for document:roadmap",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tuple_key\": { \"object\": \"document:roadmap\" }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/stores/{{store_id}}/read",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["stores", "{{store_id}}", "read"]
            },
            "description": "Reads stored relationship tuples. The tuple_key filter is optional — omit it to page through every tuple in the store; here we filter to document:roadmap. Note: /read returns directly-written tuples, not computed/inherited ones (use /expand or /check for those)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Tuple — alice owner document:roadmap",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"deletes\": {\n    \"tuple_keys\": [\n      { \"user\": \"user:alice\", \"relation\": \"owner\", \"object\": \"document:roadmap\" }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"authorization_model_id\": \"{{model_id}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/stores/{{store_id}}/write",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["stores", "{{store_id}}", "write"]
            },
            "description": "SDK: DeleteTuples. Deletes a tuple via the same /write endpoint using a 'deletes' block. After running this, re-run the Chapter 2 'alice viewer' check — it should now be DENIED."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reset Chapter 6 (delete public-memo tuples)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// OpenFGA /write is atomic AND non-idempotent for BOTH writes and",
                  "// deletes: a batch fails entirely if any tuple is already-present",
                  "// (write) or already-absent (delete). Chapter 6's two tuples can be",
                  "// in different states (e.g. alice:owner committed but the wildcard",
                  "// never did, after a failed Ch6 write). So delete each one in its OWN",
                  "// request and swallow the 'does not exist' 400 — making reset idempotent.",
                  "var base = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{base_url}}');",
                  "var store = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{store_id}}');",
                  "var model = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{model_id}}');",
                  "var tuples = [",
                  "  { user: 'user:alice', relation: 'owner', object: 'document:public-memo' },",
                  "  { user: 'user:*', relation: 'viewer', object: 'document:public-memo' }",
                  "];",
                  "tuples.forEach(function (tk) {",
                  "  pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: base + '/stores/' + store + '/write',",
                  "    method: 'POST',",
                  "    header: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },",
                  "    body: { mode: 'raw', raw: JSON.stringify({ deletes: { tuple_keys: [tk] }, authorization_model_id: model }) }",
                  "  }, function (err, res) {",
                  "    if (err) {",
                  "      console.log('reset: error deleting ' + tk.user + ' (ignored):', err);",
                  "    } else if (res.code === 200) {",
                  "      console.log('reset: deleted ' + tk.user + '#' + tk.relation + '@' + tk.object);",
                  "    } else {",
                  "      console.log('reset: ' + tk.user + ' not present (already clean), code ' + res.code);",
                  "    }",
                  "  });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tuple_key\": { \"object\": \"document:public-memo\" }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/stores/{{store_id}}/read",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["stores", "{{store_id}}", "read"]
            },
            "description": "Idempotently clears Chapter 6's tuples so its 'Write Tuples' request can be replayed on the same store.\n\nHow it works: the PRE-REQUEST SCRIPT deletes 'user:alice owner document:public-memo' and 'user:* viewer document:public-memo' in SEPARATE /write calls, ignoring the HTTP 400 'cannot delete a tuple which does not exist' for any that were never committed (OpenFGA deletes are atomic + non-idempotent, so bundling them in one /write would abort on the first missing tuple and delete nothing). The visible request then reads back document:public-memo — expect an empty 'tuples' array once both are gone.\n\nAfter this, re-run Chapter 6 → Write Tuples; it should return 200."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Store",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/stores/{{store_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["stores", "{{store_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Tears down the demo store. Run this last to clean up."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
